yCool Systems</a> | California, USA | 2016</p>\n<p>Manufacture add-ons to vapor-compression based cooling systems, which reduce their electricity usage while being CO2 neutral themselves.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2019-10-08T07:26:32.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"nglgzz/awesome-clean-tech","categoryHTML":"<h2>Companies</h2><h3>Energy</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://sonnenusa.com\">Sonnen</a> | Germany | 2010</p>\n<p>Produces energy storage solutions for households. Also, they currently provide the largest network for sharing power from renewable energies, operating in Germany.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2019-10-08T07:26:32.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"sindresorhus/awesome-npm","categoryHTML":"<h2>Tools</h2><h3>CLI</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/voidcosmos/npkill\">npkill</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/voidcosmos/npkill\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">4.5k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":4510,\"repo\":\"voidcosmos/npkill\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Easily find and remove old and heavy node_modules folders.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-10-08T06:51:38.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"sindresorhus/awesome-nodejs","categoryHTML":"<h2>Packages</h2><h3>Command-line apps</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/voidcosmos/npkill\">npkill</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/voidcosmos/npkill\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">4.5k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":4510,\"repo\":\"voidcosmos/npkill\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Easily find and remove old and heavy node_modules folders.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-10-08T06:49:56.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"0xnr/awesome-bigdata","categoryHTML":"<h2>NewSQL Databases</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/rayokota/kareldb\">KarelDB</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/rayokota/kareldb\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">362</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":362,\"repo\":\"rayokota/kareldb\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - a relational database backed by Apache Kafka.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-10-08T05:47:26.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"iCHAIT/awesome-macOS","categoryHTML":"<h2>Applications</h2><h3>Developers</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.hopperapp.com\">Hopper Dissassembler</a> - A Dissassembler for MacOS and Linux. Has a Demo option for 30 minutes of productivity.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-10-08T03:09:20.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"iCHAIT/awesome-macOS","categoryHTML":"<h2>Applications</h2><h3>Developers</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/noodlewerk/NWPusher\">Pusher</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/noodlewerk/NWPusher\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">6k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":6036,\"repo\":\"noodlewerk/NWPusher\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A free tool to do sandbox push notifications. <a href=\"https://github.com/PostgresApp/PostgresApp\"><img src=\"https://cdn.rawgit.com/iCHAIT/awesome-osx/master/media/oss.svg\" alt=\"Open-Source Software\"></a> <img src=\"https://cdn.rawgit.com/iCHAIT/awesome-osx/master/media/free.svg\" alt=\"Freeware\"></li>","updatedAt":"2019-10-08T03:07:14.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"tramcar/awesome-job-boards","categoryHTML":"<h2>Tech</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.fossjobs.net/\">Free &#x26; Open Source Jobs</a></li>","updatedAt":"2019-10-08T02:38:27.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"tramcar/awesome-job-boards","categoryHTML":"<h2>Tech</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://relocate.me/\">Relocate.me</a> - Verified relocation packages</li>","updatedAt":"2019-10-08T02:38:27.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"dariubs/GoBooks","categoryHTML":"<h2><strong>Advanced Books</strong></h2>","itemHTML":"<h3><a href=\"https://amzn.to/2Q6dLQC\">Hands-On Dependency Injection in Go</a></h3>\n<img src=\"https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/I/51%2B8EdihuKL._SX404_BO1,204,203,200_.jpg\" width=\"120px\">\n<p>Hands-On Dependency Injection in Go takes you on a journey, teaching you about refactoring existing code to adopt dependency injection (DI) using various methods available in Go.</p>\n<p>Of the six methods introduced in this book, some are conventional, such as constructor or method injection, and some unconventional, such as just-in-time or config injection. Each method is explained in detail, focusing on their strengths and weaknesses, and is followed with a step-by-step example of how to apply it. With plenty of examples, you will learn how to leverage DI to transform code into something simple and flexible.</p>\n<p>Hands-On Dependency Injection in Go takes a pragmatic approach and focuses heavily on the code, user experience, and how to achieve long-term benefits through incremental changes.</p>","updatedAt":"2019-10-08T01:47:53.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"dariubs/GoBooks","categoryHTML":"<h2><strong>Web Development</strong></h2>","itemHTML":"<h3><a href=\"https://lets-go.alexedwards.net/\">Let's Go!</a></h3>\n<img src=\"https://lets-go.alexedwards.net/sample/assets/img/cover.png\" width=\"120px\">\n<p>Let's Go teaches you step-by-step how to create fast, secure and maintainable web applications using Go. It guides you through the start-to-finish build of a real-world application — covering topics like how to structure your code, manage dependencies, authenticate and authorize users, secure your server and test your application.</p>","updatedAt":"2019-10-08T01:36:26.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"dariubs/GoBooks","categoryHTML":"<h2><strong>Web Development</strong></h2>","itemHTML":"<h3><a href=\"https://buildsaasappingo.com\">Build SaaS apps in Go</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://buildsaasappingo.com\"><img src=\"https://buildsaasappingo.com/public/basaig.jpg\" width=\"120\"></a></p>\n<p>Together, we'll build a strong, API-first, reusable codebase suitable for\nbuilding a SaaS or vanilla web application. By the end of the book you'll have\na solid framework to use as the starting point for future projects.</p>","updatedAt":"2019-10-08T01:33:06.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"dariubs/GoBooks","categoryHTML":"<h2><strong>Starter Books</strong></h2>","itemHTML":"<h3><a href=\"http://www.golang-book.com/\">An Introduction to Programming in Go</a> <em>Free</em></h3>\n<img src=\"http://www.golang-book.com/public/img/intro/cover.4194045234.png\" width=\"120px\">\n<p>This book is a short, concise introduction to computer programming using the language Go. Designed by Google, Go is a general purpose programming language with modern features, clean syntax and a robust well-documented common library, making it an ideal language to learn as your first programming language.</p>\n<p>This book is free to <a href=\"http://www.golang-book.com/\">read online</a> or <a href=\"http://www.golang-book.com/public/pdf/gobook.pdf\">pdf form</a>.</p>","updatedAt":"2019-10-08T01:26:27.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"dariubs/GoBooks","categoryHTML":"<h2><strong>Starter Books</strong></h2>","itemHTML":"<h3><a href=\"http://www.miek.nl/go\">Learning Go</a> <em>Free</em></h3>\n<img src=\"https://www.miek.nl/go/fig/bumper-inverse.png\" width=\"120px\">\n<p>A online book to start learning Golang. It features numerous exercises (and answers).</p>\n<p>The <a href=\"https://github.com/miekg/learninggo\">markdown source is available on Github</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/miekg/learninggo\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">440</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":440,\"repo\":\"miekg/learninggo\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->.</p>","updatedAt":"2019-10-08T01:26:27.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"dariubs/GoBooks","categoryHTML":"<h2><strong>Web Development</strong></h2>","itemHTML":"<h3><a href=\"https://www.usegolang.com/\">Web Development with Go: Learn to Create Real World Web Applications using Go</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://static-2.gumroad.com/res/gumroad/9387844778319/asset_previews/7446424985b5f9cb53689105d297021d/retina/Cover300ppi.png\" width=\"120px\"></a></p>\n<p>Web Development with Go was written to teach both beginners and experts how to create and deploy a real web application. You won't be building a boilerplate TODO list, but will instead be creating and deploying a production ready photo gallery application, similar to Pixieset, from scratch. The book assumes no previous web development experience and covers everything you need to know to successfully build your own web application.</p>","updatedAt":"2019-10-08T01:26:27.000Z"}]}},"pageContext":{"type":"day","from":1570492800000,"to":1570579199999,"previousId":"2019-10-09","nextId":"2019-10-07","nextName":"Oct 7th, 2019","previousName":"Oct 9th, 2019"}},"staticQueryHashes":["228695001","2744905544","4035379035"]}